You’re right—the Laplacian and the Gaussian‐smoothing operators **must stay inside** the time-limit; we should not replace them with their actions on a putative limit measure first.  
So the “difference” we care about should be written strictly as

\[
\boxed{\;
\frac{\Delta\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}(x)}
     {\rho^{\;\varepsilon}_{\,t(\varepsilon)}(x)}
\;-\;
\lim_{T\to\infty}
\frac{\Delta\mu_{T}(x)}
     {\rho^{\;\varepsilon}_{\,T}(x)}
\;}
\]

where  

\[
\rho^{\;\varepsilon}_{\,t}(x)=
\bigl(e^{\varepsilon\Delta}\mu_{t}\bigr)(x)
\quad\text{and}\quad
\Delta\mu_{t}(x)=\bigl\langle\mu_{t},\Delta_{y}\delta(x-y)\bigr\rangle .
\]

The second term keeps **both** the Laplacian and the Gaussian convolution *inside* the limit \(T\to\infty\); no operator is commuted past the limit.

\[
\boxed{\,%
\frac{\displaystyle\Delta\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}(x)}
     {\displaystyle\bigl(e^{\varepsilon\Delta}\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}\bigr)(x)}
\;-\;
\frac{\displaystyle\Delta\bigl(\,\lim_{T\to\infty}\mu_{T}\bigr)(x)}
     {\displaystyle\bigl(e^{\varepsilon\Delta}\,\lim_{T\to\infty}\mu_{T}\bigr)(x)}
\,}%
\]

Starting from  

\[
\frac{\Delta\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}(x)}{\rho_{t(\varepsilon)}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)}
\;-\;
\lim_{T\to\infty}\frac{\Delta\mu_{T}(x)}{\rho_{T}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)}
\]

keep the Laplacian **inside** the limit and pull the common limit outside the subtraction (since the first term is independent of \(T\)):

\[
= \lim_{T\to\infty}
\Biggl(
\frac{\Delta\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}(x)}{\rho_{t(\varepsilon)}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)}
-
\frac{\Delta\mu_{T}(x)}{\rho_{T}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)}
\Biggr).
\]

Combine the two fractions over a common denominator:

\[
\boxed{\;
\lim_{T\to\infty}
\frac{\;
\Delta\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}(x)\,\rho_{T}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)
-
\Delta\mu_{T}(x)\,\rho_{t(\varepsilon)}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)\;}
     {\rho_{t(\varepsilon)}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)\,\rho_{T}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)}
}.
\]

If you want to see the two error sources separately, expand the numerator once:

\[
\Delta\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}(x)\,\rho_{T}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)
-
\Delta\mu_{T}(x)\,\rho_{t(\varepsilon)}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)
=
\bigl[\Delta\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}(x)-\Delta\mu_{T}(x)\bigr]\,
      \rho_{T}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)
+\Delta\mu_{T}(x)\,
      \bigl[\rho_{T}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)-\rho_{t(\varepsilon)}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)\bigr].
\]

No further commutation is attempted; the Laplacian remains inside the time-limit, while the Gaussian convolution \(e^{\varepsilon\Delta}\) is safely outside because it commutes with weak convergence.

The difference can be rewritten by inserting the time-limit **only inside the two brackets**—nothing else moves:

\[
\boxed{%
\frac{ \displaystyle\lim_{T\to\infty}\!
       \Delta\bigl(\mu_{t(\varepsilon)}-\mu_{T}\bigr)(x)}
     {\rho_{t(\varepsilon)}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)}
\;+\;
\Delta\mu_{\infty}(x)\,
     \displaystyle\lim_{T\to\infty}
     \Bigl(
       \frac{1}{\rho_{t(\varepsilon)}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)}
       -\frac{1}{\rho_{T}^{\;\varepsilon}(x)}
     \Bigr)
} .
\]

Using a time-parametrisation \(\varepsilon(t)\downarrow0\) as \(t\to\infty\) (so that \(t=t(\varepsilon)\) and \(\varepsilon=\varepsilon(t)\) are inverses), the earlier difference can be rewritten with a **single variable \(t\)**:

\[
\boxed{%
\frac{\displaystyle\lim_{T\to\infty}
      \Delta\!\bigl(\mu_{\,t}-\mu_{\,T}\bigr)(x)}
     {\displaystyle\rho_{\,t}^{\;\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
\;+\;
\Delta\mu_{\infty}(x)\;
      \displaystyle\lim_{T\to\infty}
      \Bigl(\,
        \frac{1}{\rho_{\,t}^{\;\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
        -\frac{1}{\rho_{\,T}^{\;\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
      \Bigr)
},
\qquad
\rho_{\,s}^{\;\varepsilon(t)}(x):=
\bigl(e^{\varepsilon(t)\,\Delta}\mu_{\,s}\bigr)(x).
\]

All operators remain in their original places; only the schedule is now expressed by the monotone map \(t\mapsto\varepsilon(t)\).

\[
\boxed{%
\lim_{t\to\infty}\!
\left[
\frac{\displaystyle\lim_{T\to\infty}\Delta\!\bigl(\mu_{\,t}-\mu_{\,T}\bigr)(x)}
     {\rho_{\,t}^{\;\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
\;+\;
\Delta\mu_{\infty}(x)\,
     \displaystyle\lim_{T\to\infty}\!
     \left(
       \frac{1}{\rho_{\,t}^{\;\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
       -\frac{1}{\rho_{\,T}^{\;\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
     \right)
\right]
}
\]

Including the missing prefactor and distributing it as you asked gives

\[
\boxed{%
\lim_{t\to\infty}\!
\left[
\frac{\,\varepsilon(t)\;
       \displaystyle\lim_{T\to\infty}
       \Delta\!\bigl(\mu_{t}-\mu_{T}\bigr)(x)}
     {\rho_{t}^{\,\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
\;+\;
\varepsilon(t)\,
\Delta\mu_{\infty}(x)\;
      \displaystyle\lim_{T\to\infty}
      \Bigl(
        \frac{1}{\rho_{t}^{\,\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
        -\frac{1}{\rho_{T}^{\,\varepsilon(t)}(x)}
      \Bigr)
\right]
}
\]

with  
\[
\rho_{s}^{\,\varepsilon(t)}(x)=\bigl(e^{\varepsilon(t)\Delta}\mu_{s}\bigr)(x), 
\qquad\varepsilon(t)\downarrow0\ \text{as}\ t\to\infty.
\]

